headline: Is J&J’s 45.8% 2025 Surge Justified by Its Cash Flow and Earnings Outlook?
summary: Wondering if Johnson & Johnson is still a steady blue chip or a quietly undervalued opportunity? Let us unpack what the current share price really implies about its long term value. After drifting for a while, J&J has pushed higher recently, with the stock up 3.7% over the last week, 8.3% over the past month, and an impressive 45.8% year to date, translating into a 48.0% gain over the last year. Those kinds of moves suggest the market is rethinking its risk and growth narrative for this...
